        <abstract> 
<p>CD’s observations on the power of movement and transmission of motor impulses in plants. If RLT succeeds with the tails of mice, it will be "a beautiful little discovery"; CD will enjoy it the more "because some German sneered at natural selection and instanced the tail of the mouse" [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">10013</hi>].</p> 
        </abstract>
